[1] Washington State
Date: Thu 26 Dec 2019
Source: Washington State Department of Health [abridged, edited]
https://www.doh.wa.gov/YouandYourFamily/IllnessandDisease/Measles/Measles2019


In 2019, Washington had 2 outbreaks of measles, and one case of measles that was not part of an outbreak, totaling 87 cases. This is the most cases the state has seen since 1990. The 1st outbreak was January through May [2019] with 72 confirmed cases. The 2nd outbreak began 9 May 2019 and had 14 confirmed cases. It was declared over 28 Aug 2019.

The state is not currently in outbreak status, but measles is still circulating globally, and we could still see more cases in Washington.

Measles cases by county in 2019
-------------------------------
County / Total / Last updated
King / 13 / 19 Aug 2019
Pierce / 2 / 15 May 2019
Snohomish / 1 / 15 May 2019
Clark / 71 / 21 Nov 2019
Total / 87 / 21 Nov 2019

