Date: Mon 23 Dec 2019
Source: CBS Austin [abridged, edited]
https://cbsaustin.com/news/local/city-first-reported-case-of-measles-in-travis-county-in-20-years


Austin Public Health is reporting a person living in Travis County has been diagnosed with measles, the 1st since 1999. The department wants to warn the public who may have been at the potential exposure locations on these dates [see source URL for locations and dates].

