[3] Illinois (Chicago): O'Hare International Airport
Date: Sun 22 Dec 2019
Source: Outbreak News Today [abridged, edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/chicago-measles-possible-exposures-involve-ohare-international-airport-59337/


City of Chicago health officials are investigating possible measles exposures linked to a recent measles case in the city. [See source URL for the dates, times, and locations of possible measles exposures that may have occurred on 12-17 Dec 2019.]

The Chicago Department of Public Health (CDPH) says they have one of the highest measles, mumps and rubella (MMR) vaccination rates in the nation, meaning that most children and adults in Chicago are vaccinated and protected.

Between 2011 and 2019, there have been several confirmed cases of measles in Chicago, largely related to international travel. Most individuals in Chicago are protected from measles because they were vaccinated as children.

